<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7617540>
    dc:description "Figure 42. Paracanthopoma vampyra, n. sp., holotype,MZUSP 86953, 14.6 mm SL.Brazil, Amazonas, Rio Preto da Eva, Igarapé Sucuriju.(A) Lateral view of body; (B) Dorsal view of head;(C) ventral view of head. flattened. Eye large (Fig. 42), without free orbital rim, lo- specimens examined. Anterior nostril small, surround- cated dorsolaterally on head and directed dorsolaterally, ed by short tubule of integument produced posteriorly with pronounced lateral component. Integument over into small pointed process, with double elastin cores. eye thin and transparent. Middle of eye slightly anterior Anterior internarial width slightly larger than interorbital. to middle of HL, interorbital width approximately 70% of Posterior naris slightly larger than anterior one, round- longitudinal diameter of eye. Eyelens large, constricted ish or triangular in shape, adjacent to mesial margin of by iris only marginally, with large round or oval pupil, in eye and partly occluded by anterior flap of integument. Anterior margin of posterior naris posterior to transverse Table 13. Morphometric data of Paracanthopoma vampyra. Ranges, mean line through anterior margin of eyes. Posterior internarial and SD include holotype. Head subunits were obtained with an ocular mi- width narrower than interorbital and slightly larger than crometer and therefore as projections. Abbreviations: min = minimum diameter of one nostril. value; max = maximum value; n = number of specimens; SD = standard Opercular odontodophore medium-sized and elon- deviation. gate, dorsolaterally located on head, on dorsal half of head depth in lateral view, anterodorsally to pectoral-fin" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7617540/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7617448>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Comparative chart of jaws and anterior portion of head of Paracanthopoma species, cleared and stained specimens, ventral views: (A) Pc. ahriman FMNH 105525;(B)Pc.alleynei MZUSP 103052;(C) Pc.cangussu MZUSP 86250;(D)Pc.capeta MZUSP 29154;(E) Pc.daemon MZUSP 95597;(F)Pc.irritans INPA 20529; (G) Pc.malevola MCP 36217;(H) Pc.parva MZUSP 30400;(I) Pc.saci MZUSP 125626; (J) Pc.satanica MZUSP 100149;(K) Pc.truculenta MZUSP 30404;(L) Pc.vampyra MZUSP 100138. Scale bars = 500 μm. Pc.carrapata not shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7617448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7617542>
    dc:description "Figure 43. Paracanthopoma vampyra, holotype,MZUSP 86953,CT scan images of head skeleton,(A) Lateral;(B) Dorsal;(C)Ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7617542/files/figure.png" ;
